## Background and Motivation

Current roslyn syntax lists (SyntaxList, SeparatedSyntaxList, SyntaxTriviaList, SyntaxNodeOrTokenList, SnytaxTokenList) can only be constructed by using SyntaxFactory.  This is extremely verbose (needing to prefix with SYntaxFactory) and annoying.  To make a list containing one element, you need to also use SyntaxFactory.SingletonXXXList, but for zero to N values you use SyntaxFactory.List(someCollection).

All these apis should be updated to support collection expressions by way of the CollectionBuilderAttribute.

## Proposed API

```diff
+ public static class SyntaxList
+ {
+    public static SyntaxList<TNode> Create<TNode>(ReadOnlySpan<TNode> nodes) where TNode : SyntaxNode
+ }

+ [CollectionAttribute(typeof(SyntaxList), "Create")]
public readonly struct SyntaxList<TNode>
{
}
```

This would make things much nicer.  For example:

````
// Empty list:
Block(openBrace, [], closeBrace)

// Singleton list:
Block(openBrace, [embeddedStatement], closeBrace);

// Joining lists:
Block(openBrace, [.. initialStatements, .. newStatements], closeBrace);

// etc.
```

